<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Jq on Mike Ball</title><link>/tags/jq/</link><description>Recent content in Jq on Mike Ball</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 02 Oct 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="/tags/jq/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Querying GitHub Release Data With gh and jq</title><link>/blog/querying-github-release-data-with-gh-and-jq/</link><pubDate>Sun, 02 Oct 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/blog/querying-github-release-data-with-gh-and-jq/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A demo of semi-advanced &lt;code&gt;gh&lt;/code&gt; CLI and &lt;code&gt;jq&lt;/code&gt; querying techniques.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="problem"&gt;Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;d like to list the latest patch release associated with each of the latest 5 minor versions of Grafana represented as a JSON array.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-json" data-lang="json"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;9.1.6&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;9.0.9&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;8.5.13&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;8.4.11&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;8.3.11&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solution"&gt;Solution&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leverage that&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grafana releases are published as &lt;a href="https://github.com/grafana/grafana/releases"&gt;GitHub releases&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The &lt;a href="https://cli.github.com/"&gt;gh&lt;/a&gt; CLI supports an &lt;code&gt;api&lt;/code&gt; command, enabling users to query GitHub API endpoints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The GitHub API supports a &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/rest/releases/releases#list-releases"&gt;list releases&lt;/a&gt; endpoint&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;gh api&lt;/code&gt; supports a &lt;code&gt;--jq&lt;/code&gt; flag, enabling the ability to invoke &lt;code&gt;jq&lt;/code&gt; queries against GitHub API responses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>